│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The SDK Manager installation failed during the **target_install (apt)**     │
│ stage. The actual error is on the second line of the log:                   │
│                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                         │
│ E: Unable to locate package nvidia-jetpack=6.1*                             │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ This error indicates that `apt-get` cannot find the `nvidia-jetpack=6.1*`   │
│ package in the configured NVIDIA repositories. The log does not show a      │
│ prior `apt update` command, which is the mandatory first step per           │
│                                                                             │
│ NVIDIA documentation requiring installation of the public key and adding    │
│ the appropriate x86_64 repository to the host system's source list before   │
│ attempting installation                                                     │
│                                                                             │
│ . The most common causes are:                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ 1. **Missing or stale package cache**: The target system has not run `apt   │
│ update` after system boot                                                   │
│ 2. **Misconfigured repository sources**: The                                │
│ `/etc/apt/sources.list.d/nvidia-l4t-apt-source.list` file is missing or     │
│ points to an incorrect repository URL/release version                       │
│ 3. **Missing GPG key**: The NVIDIA repository public key has not been       │
│ installed                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # On the target Jetson device, run the following in order:                  │
│                                                                             │
│ # 1. Install the NVIDIA repository public key                               │
│ sudo apt-key adv --fetch-key                                                │
│ http://repo.download.nvidia.com/jetson/jetson-ota-public.asc                │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Update the package cache (REQUIRED before install)                     │
│ sudo apt update                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. Verify the nvidia-jetpack package is now visible                       │
│ apt-cache policy nvidia-jetpack                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. Install JetPack 6.1 (now that repo is configured)                      │
│ sudo apt-get install nvidia-jetpack=6.1*                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ # 5. If that specific version match fails, install latest available         │
│ sudo apt-get install nvidia-jetpack                                         │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ NVIDIA JetPack documentation explicitly states the first step is to install │
│ the public key of the x86_64 repository of the public APT server            │
│                                                                             │
│ , then add the appropriate repository URL. The `apt update` command         │
│ rebuilds the local package cache from the remote repository after the       │
│ source list is configured.                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ Multiple NVIDIA Developer Forum posts                                       │
│ ((https://forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/unable-to-locate-package-nvidia-jet │
│ pack-on-orin-devkit/210894),                                                │
│ (https://forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/unable-to-install-jetpack-on-orin-de │
│ vkit/265934)) document users encountering this identical "Unable to locate  │
│ package nvidia-jetpack" error and resolving it by ensuring                  │
│                                                                             │
│ the `sudo apt update` command was executed prior to the installation        │
│ command                                                                     │
│                                                                             │
│ . The version wildcard `6.1*` may also be too strict if the repository      │
│ contains newer revisions; removing the version constraint allows apt to     │
│ install the latest available version.                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ - **`sudo apt-key adv`** requires root privileges; use only on systems you  │
│ control.                                                                    │
│ - **`apt update`** refreshes all configured repositories (safe operation,   │
│ no installation).                                                           │
│ - **`apt-get install`** will download and install packages; ensure          │
│ sufficient disk space on the target device (typically 5–10 GB for full      │
│ JetPack).                                                                   │
│ - Do **not** run these commands during active system use or critical        │
│ processes; reboot or halt other services first if possible.                 │
│ - The version wildcard `=6.1*` may fail if the repository contains only     │
│ `6.2` or later; in that case, remove the version constraint and accept the  │
│ latest available version, or check                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ the appropriate repository URL for the correct release number (r36.4 for    │
│ JetPack 6.1)                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
