│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ a critical flash failure during the JetPack installation process on the     │
│ device communication stage. The error "failed to flash, errCode 1042" with  │
│ "NvDeviceFlashFail" indicates the target Jetson device lost connection or   │
│ was not in the proper recovery state when the flash utility attempted to    │
│ write the OS image                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ . Error code 1042 is a device-level communication failure—the flash utility │
│ could not interact with the target device at the hardware/bootloader level  │
│ during the write operation.                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Power off the Jetson device completely                                 │
│ sudo poweroff  # If it still boots; otherwise unplug power                  │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Enter Force Recovery Mode (example for Xavier/Orin devices):           │
│ #    - Locate the Force Recovery button/jumper on your board                │
│ #    - While holding Force Recovery, press/apply power                      │
│ #    - Release Power button, then Force Recovery after 2 seconds            │
│ #    - For jumper-based boards: short pins 9-10 on J50, apply power via J48 │
│ #    - Verify with: lsusb | grep -i nvidia                                  │
│ #    # Should see: ID 0955:7523 NVIDIA Corp. APX (or similar)               │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. Use a direct USB cable (not hub) in a USB 2.0 or 3.0 port              │
│ #    - Avoid USB hubs during flashing                                       │
│ #    - Test with a different high-quality cable if available                │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. Disconnect unnecessary USB peripherals                                 │
│ #    - Keep only HDMI monitor and power connected                           │
│ #    - Unplug any external storage or USB devices from the Jetson           │
│                                                                             │
│ # 5. Retry the flash operation in SDK Manager                               │
│ #    - Start a fresh SDK Manager session                                    │
│ #    - Ensure the device shows in recovery mode (APX device visible in      │
│ lsusb)                                                                      │
│ #    - Begin the flashing process again                                     │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Error 1042 typically results from USB connection instability or the device  │
│ not being in proper recovery mode. The recovery mode entry procedure and    │
│ direct USB connection (avoiding hubs) are documented as essential           │
│ prerequisites                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ NVIDIA's official troubleshooting guidance emphasizes ensuring the device   │
│ is properly set to Force Recovery Mode, checking physical connections, and  │
│ using different USB cables/ports as the primary steps                       │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Reconnecting power after re-entering recovery mode, confirming adequate     │
│ power supply, and switching to high-quality USB-C/Type-B cables (shorter    │
│ than 1.5m) resolve most flash failures                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Sources:                                                                    │
│ - https://wiki.seeedstudio.com/usb_timeout_during_flash/                    │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://nvidia-jetson.piveral.com/jetson-orin-nano/sdk-manager-cli-error-un │
│ able-to-detect-nvidia-jetson-device-via-usb/                                │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ **⚠️ Risks:**                                                               │
│ - **Power loss**: Running `poweroff` on a hung system may leave storage in  │
│ an inconsistent state. If the device is unresponsive, unplug the power      │
│ supply instead.                                                             │
│ - **Physical jumper/button**: Force Recovery mode entry requires physical   │
│ access to the board. Incorrect jumper placement can prevent recovery mode   │
│ and may require UART serial access to diagnose further.                     │
│ - **USB device detection**: On virtual machines or Windows with WSL, USB    │
│ passthrough may fail.                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ A native physical Ubuntu host is strongly recommended for flashing; avoid   │
│ VMs, Docker, and WSL                                                        │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ **When NOT to run these steps:**                                            │
│ - If the Jetson is physically unreachable (in a remote deployment), you     │
│ will need serial UART console access.                                       │
│ - If you cannot reliably enter Force Recovery Mode despite multiple         │
│ attempts, the bootloader may be corrupted and require vendor RMA or         │
│ UART-based recovery (beyond SDK Manager scope).                             │
