│ I'll analyze this SDK Manager failure systematically.                       │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Analysis of Log                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows:                                                              │
│ - **Error line:** `Connection timed out` (repeated 3 times)                 │
│ - **Retry behavior:** `Retrying (1/3)` and `Retrying (2/3)` indicate the    │
│ tool attempted recovery                                                     │
│ - **Failure stage:** `Install aborted at stage: download`                   │
│ - **Root cause:** Network connectivity issue during the download phase      │
│                                                                             │
│ The tool made 3 attempts to reach a remote resource but all failed with     │
│ connection timeouts, ultimately aborting the installation.                  │
│                                                                             │
│ Now let me search for official NVIDIA guidance on this specific failure:    │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me search for more specific troubleshooting guidance on network and     │
│ proxy issues:                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ a connection timed out error, which occurs when SDK Manager cannot          │
│ establish a connection to a server within a set time limit, usually         │
│ pointing to server overload, network issues, or firewall blocks             │
│                                                                             │
│ . Specifically, the log shows three consecutive `Connection timed out`      │
│ failures during the `download` stage, with SDK Manager making 3 retry       │
│ attempts before aborting (`Retrying (1/3)` and `Retrying (2/3)` → `Install  │
│ aborted at stage: download`). This indicates the tool was unable to reach   │
│ NVIDIA's download servers to fetch SDK components.                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. (Windows) Temporarily disable Windows Firewall to test connectivity    │
│ #    Settings > Update & Security > Windows Security > Firewall & network   │
│ protection                                                                  │
│ #    Toggle off for testing only                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Verify network connectivity to NVIDIA servers                          │
│ ping -c 4 nvidia.com                                                        │
│ curl -v https://developer.nvidia.com                                        │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. If behind a corporate proxy, configure SDK Manager:                    │
│ #    - Launch SDK Manager                                                   │
│ #    - Click ⋮ (three dots) > Settings                                      │
│ #    - Go to Proxy Settings > Manual Configuration                          │
│ #    - Enter your proxy server IP, port, and credentials                    │
│ #    - Click Apply                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. Clear SDK Manager cache and retry                                      │
│ #    (On Windows) Delete: C:\Users\<USERNAME>\AppData\Local\Temp\sdkm_*     │
│                                                                             │
│ # 5. Retry the installation                                                 │
│ #    Restart SDK Manager and attempt download again                         │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Timeout errors during SDK Manager downloads are typically firewall issues;  │
│ disabling the firewall and restarting SDK Manager can resolve the problem   │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Network issues and unstable internet access—particularly in proxy           │
│ environments—are common causes of SDK Manager connectivity errors           │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ NVIDIA's official SDK Manager documentation specifies that proxy            │
│ environments require explicit configuration via the Settings dialog, where  │
│ you can choose System Configuration mode (which reads HTTPS_PROXY           │
│ environment variables) or Manual Configuration mode                         │
│                                                                             │
│ . Clearing the temporary cache removes any corrupted partial downloads that │
│ might cause retry logic to fail.                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ **Risk:** Disabling Windows Firewall (step 1) globally is a security        │
│ exposure. Only disable it temporarily for testing—re-enable it immediately  │
│ afterward or use more granular firewall rules to permit SDK Manager         │
│ specifically instead. Do **not** leave it disabled long-term in production  │
│ environments.                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ If you are behind a corporate proxy, confirm the proxy credentials and      │
│ server address with your IT department before entering them; incorrect      │
│ credentials will cause continued timeouts. Test network connectivity (step  │
│ 2) as a non-destructive diagnostic first before proceeding to               │
│ firewall/proxy changes.                                                     │
