│ Windows-specific remediation, and diagnostic procedures. Let me compile the │
│ diagnosis and recommendations.                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows `curl: (6) Could not resolve host: developer.nvidia.com`,     │
│ which means curl reached the hostname lookup stage and the system could not │
│ turn that name into an IP address.                                          │
│                                                                             │
│  The SDK Manager installation **aborted at the download stage** when it     │
│ attempted to retrieve package components from NVIDIA's servers. This is     │
│ fundamentally a DNS (Domain Name System) resolution failure on the host     │
│ system — the Windows machine cannot translate "developer.nvidia.com" into a │
│ usable IP address.                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # Step 1: Flush the Windows DNS resolver cache (run as Administrator)       │
│ ipconfig /flushdns                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 2: Verify the system has active network connectivity                 │
│ nslookup developer.nvidia.com                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 3: If nslookup fails, test basic connectivity with a known-good IP   │
│ ping 8.8.8.8                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 4: If Step 3 succeeds but Step 2 fails, restart the Windows DNS      │
│ Client service                                                              │
│ net stop dnscache                                                           │
│ net start dnscache                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 5: Retry the nslookup to confirm resolution works                    │
│ nslookup developer.nvidia.com                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 6: Re-run SDK Manager after DNS resolution succeeds                  │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Flushing the Windows DNS resolver cache using `ipconfig /flushdns` clears   │
│ stale DNS records and forces Windows to query the DNS server again.         │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The `nslookup` command fetches the DNS records for a given domain name by   │
│ querying DNS servers directly.                                              │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ If ping to an IP address succeeds but nslookup fails, the issue is DNS; if  │
│ both fail, the problem is network-level (Wi-Fi, Ethernet, router, firewall, │
│ or internet connection).                                                    │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Because nslookup doesn't use the client's DNS cache, name resolution will   │
│ use a fresh query to the DNS server.                                        │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ These steps follow guidance from:                                           │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-03-20-flush-dns-resolver-cache-ipconfi │
│ g/view                                                                      │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/networking/dns/troubleshoo │
│ t/troubleshoot-dns-client                                                   │
│ - https://forums.developer.nvidia.com (verified SDK Manager network         │
│ failures are DNS-related)                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ **No destructive commands.** All steps are safe: `ipconfig /flushdns` only  │
│ clears cached DNS lookups (they rebuild on next use), and restarting the    │
│ dnscache service is a standard Windows troubleshooting procedure that does  │
│ not affect files, network settings, or saved credentials. However, **`net   │
│ stop` and `net start` require Administrator privileges** — you must run     │
│ Command Prompt or PowerShell as Administrator. If Step 2 (`nslookup         │
│ developer.nvidia.com`) succeeds immediately after Step 1, skip Steps 3–5    │
│ and proceed directly to re-running SDK Manager. If Steps 1–5 fail and the   │
│ system still cannot resolve **any** domain (test with `nslookup             │
│ google.com`), the problem is upstream: check network adapter status,        │
│ Wi-Fi/Ethernet connectivity, router, firewall rules, or contact your ISP —  │
│ this is beyond SDK Manager scope.                                           │
