│ JetPack 6.1                                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ . Specifically, the error message `"checksum mismatch for                   │
│ jetpack-6.1.tar.gz: expected abc, got def"` indicates that SDK Manager      │
│ downloaded the file but the calculated SHA hash does not match NVIDIA's     │
│ published checksum. This causes the install to abort at the download stage  │
│ before any installation begins.                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ This is a known issue reported by users installing JetPack 6.1 via SDK      │
│ Manager                                                                     │
│                                                                             │
│ , typically caused by a corrupted or incomplete download, stale cached      │
│ metadata, or transient network issues during the transfer.                  │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Delete the SDK Manager state directory (contains corrupted metadata)   │
│ rm -rf ~/.nvsdkm                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Delete the download cache directory                                    │
│ rm -rf ~/Downloads/nvidia/sdkm_downloads                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. Restart SDK Manager (will reinitialize configuration)                  │
│ sdkmanager                                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. Re-run the JetPack 6.1 installation from the GUI                       │
│ # Select your target board, confirm JetPack 6.1, and allow a clean          │
│ re-download                                                                 │
