│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows `dpkg: error processing package nvidia-l4t-bsp (--configure)` │
│ during the `target_install` stage, indicating the package configuration     │
│ phase failed                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ . This is a half-configured package state where the `nvidia-l4t-bsp` (Board │
│ Support Package) encountered an error during its post-installation          │
│ configuration script. The error did not occur during download or unpacking, │
│ but during the actual configuration step—a common failure pattern in        │
│ JetPack installations when bootloader/BSP post-install procedures fail.     │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Diagnose the broken package state                                      │
│ sudo dpkg --audit                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Fix broken dependencies and force overwrite conflicting files          │
│ sudo apt update                                                             │
│ sudo apt install --fix-broken -o Dpkg::Options::="--force-overwrite"        │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. Retry the installation/upgrade                                         │
│ sudo apt dist-upgrade                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. If still failing, clean and restart                                    │
│ sudo apt clean                                                              │
│ sudo apt update                                                             │
│ sudo apt install --fix-broken -o Dpkg::Options::="--force-overwrite"        │
│                                                                             │
│ # 5. Finally, reboot                                                        │
│ sudo reboot                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ NVIDIA's official JetPack documentation recommends using `sudo apt install  │
│ --fix-broken -o Dpkg::Options::="--force-overwrite"` to resolve dpkg        │
│ configuration errors during the target_install phase                        │
│                                                                             │
│  (https://docs.nvidia.com/jetson/jetpack/install-setup/index.html). The     │
│ `--fix-broken` flag instructs apt to attempt to correct a system with       │
│ broken dependencies, while `--force-overwrite` allows dpkg to overwrite     │
│ files from other packages if necessary—this is essential when multiple L4T  │
│ packages compete for the same files.                                        │
│                                                                             │
│ The `dpkg --audit` command identifies packages that are half-configured     │
│ (failed previous configuration) so they can be retried using `dpkg          │
│ --configure`                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ . The sequence recovers the broken package database state so the BSP        │
│ configuration scripts can execute cleanly.                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ **⚠️ SUDO / DESTRUCTIVE**: All commands use `sudo` and modify system        │
│ package state. **Do not run `--force-overwrite` unless you understand file  │
│ conflicts**—it can overwrite legitimate files if package versions are       │
│ severely mismatched. The `--fix-broken` flag is safe but may remove         │
│ packages if dependency resolution requires it. **Do not interrupt these     │
│ commands** once started—canceling mid-install can worsen the broken state.  │
│ Always **test on a non-production device first**, or have a backup of your  │
│ JetPack installation. If the error persists after these steps, the device   │
│ may need re-flashing via SDK Manager or recovery mode.                      │
