│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows the install aborted at the flash stage with the error "No     │
│ NVIDIA device found in recovery mode"                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ . This is a **device detection failure** during flashing—the SDK Manager's  │
│ flash tool could not detect the Jetson developer board via USB when it      │
│ attempted to begin the flash operation. The Jetson device either was not    │
│ properly placed into recovery mode, was not correctly connected via USB to  │
│ the host, or the host computer does not have the proper drivers/permissions │
│ to detect the NVIDIA vendor ID (0955) on the USB bus.                       │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # Step 1: Verify your Jetson board model and locate its recovery mode pins  │
│ # (Consult your Jetson's user guide for exact pin locations—they vary by    │
│ model)                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 2: Power off the device completely                                   │
│ sudo poweroff  # on the Jetson itself, if accessible                        │
│ # OR manually disconnect power                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 3: Place the jumper to short REC and GND pins                        │
│ # For most boards (Orin, Xavier NX/AGX, Nano):                              │
│ # - Power off completely                                                    │
│ # - Locate FC REC and GND pins on the button header (J14, J12, or J40       │
│ depending on model)                                                         │
│ # - Connect a jumper wire between FC REC and GND                            │
│ # - Plug in power (device will boot into recovery mode automatically)       │
│ # - Keep the jumper in place during the entire flash process                │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 4: Connect USB and verify detection on the host                      │
│ lsusb -d '0955:'  # Check for NVIDIA device (vendor ID 0955)                │
│                                                                             │
│ # Expected output (one of these):                                           │
│ # ID 0955:7020  (means device is running Linux, NOT in recovery)            │
│ # ID 0955:7023  (Jetson Nano in recovery)                                   │
│ # ID 0955:7323  (Jetson Orin NX in recovery)                                │
│ # ID 0955:7423  (Jetson Orin Nano in recovery)                              │
│ # ID 0955:7f21  (older Jetson Nano variant)                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 5: If device appears, retry SDK Manager flashing                     │
│ # If device does NOT appear:                                                │
│ # - Try different USB cable (test with USB 3.0 or higher if possible)       │
│ # - Try different USB port on host                                          │
│ # - Use native Ubuntu (not VM) on the host                                  │
│ # - Verify jumper is properly seated                                        │
│ # - Power cycle: unplug, wait 5 seconds, plug in again                      │
│                                                                             │
│ # Step 6: After successful flash, remove the jumper from REC/GND            │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The Jetson board requires a jumper to short the REC and GND pins, then      │
│ power reconnection to enter recovery mode. Recovery mode is confirmed by    │
│ running lsusb on the host and seeing an NVIDIA device with vendor ID 0955   │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Using a native Ubuntu installation (not a VM), ensuring the host is         │
│ up-to-date, and testing with high-quality USB 3.0+ cables and different USB │
│ ports are standard fixes for device detection failures                      │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ If lsusb shows ID 0955:7020 (Linux for Tegra running), the device is NOT in │
│ recovery mode and the procedure must be retried                             │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ - **Jumper placement is critical**: Using the wrong pins will not enable    │
│ recovery mode and may damage the board if you short unintended pins. Always │
│ consult your specific Jetson model's user guide before touching any         │
│ hardware.                                                                   │
│ - **Power handling**: Never connect/disconnect USB or jumpers while the     │
│ device is powered on unless explicitly instructed. Always power off         │
│ completely before placing jumpers.                                          │
│ - **Host environment**: Flashing **must** be done from a native Linux       │
│ installation (Ubuntu 20.04, 22.04, or 24.04 on a real machine), not from a  │
│ Windows/macOS host or a virtual machine, as SDK Manager relies on native    │
│ USB device drivers.                                                         │
│ - **If lsusb still shows no device after multiple attempts**, the board may │
│ have corrupted bootloader code                                              │
│ (https://forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/jetson-not-seen-using-lsusb-in-force │
│ d-recovery-mode/221928). In that case, contact NVIDIA support.              │
