│ ---                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows the failure "BootRom is not Running" followed by recovery     │
│ attempts that fail, indicating the flashing tool lost communication with    │
│ the target board's bootloader at the critical "Boot Rom communication"      │
│ phase of the flash stage.                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│  This prevents SDK Manager from sending the initial Recovery Code Module    │
│ (RCM) that instructs the BootRom to load the flash applet. The most common  │
│ causes are: the target device is not in proper Force Recovery Mode, the USB │
│ connection is unreliable, or recovery mode was not correctly initiated.     │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ The recovery mode entry procedure varies by Jetson model. Use one of the    │
│ following based on your board:                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ **For Jetson Nano (simplest method):**                                      │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Power off the device and disconnect power                              │
│ # 2. Locate FC REC and GND pins (under the heatsink, near SD card)          │
│ # 3. Use a jumper to short FC REC to GND                                    │
│ # 4. Reconnect power (device will boot into recovery mode automatically)    │
│ # 5. Verify recovery mode detection:                                        │
│ lsusb | grep NVIDIA                                                         │
│ # Should show NVIDIA device (ID 0955:xxxx)                                  │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ **For Jetson Xavier / Orin (button method):**                               │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Disconnect power                                                       │
│ # 2. Connect USB Type-C cable to host computer                              │
│ # 3. Press and hold the FORCE RECOVERY button                               │
│ # 4. While holding, press and release RESET button                          │
│ # 5. Release FORCE RECOVERY button                                          │
│ # 6. Verify recovery mode:                                                  │
│ lsusb | grep NVIDIA                                                         │
│ # Should show NVIDIA device                                                 │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ **For devices that previously booted Linux:**                               │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # Optional: attempt remote recovery mode entry                              │
│ ssh <user>@<jetson-ip>                                                      │
│ sudo reboot forced-recovery                                                 │
│ # Then run SDK Manager flash                                                │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ **Before retry:**                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Try a different USB port (preferably USB 3.0+)                         │
│ # 2. Test with a high-quality USB cable                                     │
│ # 3. Delete and re-download SDK Manager flash files                         │
│ # 4. Ensure host has ≥25GB free disk space (not on virtual machine if       │
│ possible)                                                                   │
│ sudo lsusb -d 0955: -v | grep -E "Bus|Device|bcdDevice"                     │
│ # Verify board shows with correct NVIDIA vendor ID (0955)                   │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The recovery mode entry method—either via software reboot with `sudo reboot │
│ forced-recovery` or using reset and recovery buttons—allows the device to   │
│ enter BootRom recovery state, during which it should be detected by USB     │
│ with ID 0955:7c18 (for TX2) or similar NVIDIA IDs.                          │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Poor quality or damaged USB cables, or host machine configuration           │
│ (especially virtual machines), can prevent proper communication between     │
│ host and device during recovery mode.                                       │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Deleting and re-downloading flash files helps recover from corrupted        │
│ installation packs, and ensuring adequate disk space (≥25GB) prevents       │
│ truncated images.                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│  For more information, consult:                                             │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://docs.nvidia.com/jetson/archives/r35.4.1/DeveloperGuide/text/SD/Flas │
│ hingSupport.html                                                            │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/flashing-with-sdk-manager-stuck-in-bo │
│ otrom-not-running/232457                                                    │
│ -                                                                           │
│ https://nvidia-jetson.piveral.com/jetson-orin-nano/jetson-orin-nano-develop │
│ er-kit-not-detected-in-recovery-mode/                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ **⚠️ DESTRUCTIVE:** Flashing erases all data on the target device's         │
│ internal storage (eMMC). Back up any data before proceeding. **⚠️ SUDO:**   │
│ All commands require elevated privileges. Do **not** run on a virtual       │
│ machine unless unavoidable—physical USB passthrough and native Linux are    │
│ required for reliable BootRom communication. Do **not** disconnect or reset │
│ the device mid-flash, as this may corrupt the bootloader. Physically        │
│ inspect the recovery mode pins/buttons and jumper placement to ensure they  │
│ are in the correct locations for your specific board revision (pin          │
