│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis Analysis                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows two critical lines:                                           │
│ - `Authentication failed`                                                   │
│ - `Install aborted at stage: license`                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ The failure occurred during the **license authentication stage** of the SDK │
│ Manager installation. This indicates that SDK Manager could not validate    │
│ the user's NVIDIA account credentials or license entitlements needed to     │
│ proceed with the installation.                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me search for expert guidance on this specific failure:                 │
│                                                                             │
│ Now let me search for more specific remediation steps from official NVIDIA  │
│ documentation:                                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me search for more specific guidance on Windows SDK Manager login       │
│ failures and remediation:                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Based on my investigation, I now have enough information to provide a       │
│ complete diagnosis and remediation.                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Diagnosis                                                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The log shows two critical failure lines: `Authentication failed` followed  │
│ by `Install aborted at stage: license`. This indicates that SDK Manager     │
│ attempted to authenticate the user's NVIDIA Developer credentials during    │
│ the license validation stage, but the authentication failed. The            │
│ installation was aborted before it could proceed past the license step.     │
│                                                                             │
│ Common related SDK Manager authentication errors include "User is not       │
│ authorized on NVIDIA Dev server"                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ , suggesting credential validation or account authorization issues at the   │
│ NVIDIA authentication service.                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Recommended fix                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # 1. Clear cached SDK Manager credentials and configuration                 │
│ # Windows (PowerShell as Admin):                                            │
│ Remove-Item -Path "$env:APPDATA\.nvsdkm" -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction       │
│ SilentlyContinue                                                            │
│ Remove-Item -Path "$env:LOCALAPPDATA\NVIDIA" -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction   │
│ SilentlyContinue                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ # 2. Log out from SDK Manager (if you have it open)                         │
│ # Open SDK Manager and click "Logout" button, or use CLI:                   │
│ "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA Corporation\SDK Manager\NvSDKManager.exe" --logout │
│                                                                             │
│ # 3. Restart the SDK Manager application and attempt login again            │
│ # Use browser-based authentication (most reliable):                         │
│ # - Select "devzone" login type when prompted                               │
│ # - A URL will appear—open it in a web browser on ANY device                │
│ # - Enter your NVIDIA developer.nvidia.com credentials                      │
│ # - Complete 2FA if required                                                │
│ # - Confirm device login in the browser                                     │
│ # - Return to SDK Manager after successful authentication                   │
│                                                                             │
│ # 4. If step 3 still fails, verify your account status:                     │
│ # Visit https://developer.nvidia.com directly                               │
│ # Log in and confirm your account is active                                 │
│ # Check if your account was blocked (unlikely but check account email)      │
│ # If blocked, use the "Unlock Account" link sent to your registered email   │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Why this works                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ Clearing SDK Manager cache and configuration is a documented                │
│ troubleshooting step for authentication failures                            │
│                                                                             │
│ . Stale or corrupted credential tokens in the local cache are a common      │
│ cause of "Authentication failed" errors.                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ Some users report login token validation failures within SDK Manager even   │
│ when web login works                                                        │
│                                                                             │
│ , confirming that the issue is often local cache corruption rather than     │
│ account problems.                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ The browser-based authentication method is the most reliable approach,      │
│ allowing credential entry on any device and returning control to SDK        │
│ Manager once verification is complete                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ .                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ ## Risks / when not to run                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ The first command uses `Remove-Item` with `-Force` flag—ensure you run      │
│ PowerShell as Administrator, and be aware this irreversibly deletes cached  │
│ settings. SDK Manager will regenerate these directories on next launch.     │
│ **Do not** delete files from `C:\Program Files\NVIDIA Corporation` itself,  │
│ as this will break the SDK Manager installation. The `--logout` command is  │
│ safe to run even if you're not currently logged in. If your NVIDIA          │
│ Developer account is blocked (you'll see an email), use the unlock link in  │
│ that email before retrying login steps.                                     │
